#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.105"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.105:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.105:0.2"
msgid "11. Yogakkhemivagga"
msgstr "11. Sanctuary"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.105:0.3"
msgid "105. Upādāyasutta"
msgstr "105. Because of Grasping"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:1.1"
msgid "“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati kiṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhan”ti?"
msgstr "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what, do pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:2.1"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …."
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:3.1"
msgid "“Cakkhusmiṃ kho, bhikkhave, sati cakkhuṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "“Mendicants, when there’s an eye, because of grasping the eye, pleasure and pain arise in oneself. …"

msgctxt "sn35.105:3.2"
msgid "manasmiṃ sati manaṃ upādāya uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhaṃ."
msgstr "When there’s a mind, because of grasping the mind, pleasure and pain arise in oneself."

msgctxt "sn35.105:3.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn35.105:3.4"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:4.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:5.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:6.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:7.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya uppajjeyya ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhan”ti?"
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:8.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe …."
msgstr "“No, sir.” …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.86"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:9.1"
msgid "“Jivhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is the ear … nose … tongue … body …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:10.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:11.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:12.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:13.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya uppajjeyya ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhan”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:14.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe …."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:15.1"
msgid "“Mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?"
msgstr "mind permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:16.1"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:17.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:18.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:19.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya uppajjeyya ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhan”ti?"
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would pleasure and pain arise in oneself?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:20.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.105:21.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … manasmimpi nibbindati."
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "sn35.105:21.2"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn35.105:21.3"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.105:21.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
